
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lintian` baraye baresi kardan package-haye Debian (ya .deb file-ha) az nazar moshkelat va ghalat-haye ehtemali estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta az dorost va standard boodan package-ha etminan hosel konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lintian package.deb` -->  📦 Baresi yek package .deb khass.
    🔹 `lintian --verbose package.deb` --> 🗣️ Namayesh etela'at bishtar dar morede moshkelat va warning-ha.
    🔹 `lintian --pedantic package.deb` -->  🧐 Baresi daghigh-tar va hosastar.
    🔹 `lintian --no-tags package.deb` --> 🏷️ Hazf tag-haye etela'ati az khorooji (faqat moshkelat va warning-ha).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ lintian mypackage.deb

    🔹 Baresi package `mypackage.deb` az nazar moshkelat.

    $ lintian --verbose mypackage.deb

    🔹 Namayesh detailate bishtar dar morede moshkelati ke peyda shode.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ lintian --no-tags mypackage.deb

    🔹 Faghat error-ha va warning-ha namayesh dade mishavand, va etela'at digar hazf mishavad, baraye inke khorooji sade-tar bashad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lintian` command is used to check Debian packages (or .deb files) for potential issues and errors. It helps you ensure that your packages are correct and meet the Debian standards.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lintian package.deb` --> 📦 Check a specific .deb package.
    🔹 `lintian --verbose package.deb` --> 🗣️ Show more detailed information about problems and warnings.
    🔹 `lintian --pedantic package.deb` --> 🧐 Perform a more thorough and strict check.
    🔹 `lintian --no-tags package.deb` --> 🏷️ Remove informational tags from the output (only show errors and warnings).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ lintian mypackage.deb

    🔹 Check the `mypackage.deb` package for issues.

    $ lintian --verbose mypackage.deb

    🔹 Show more details about the problems found.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ lintian --no-tags mypackage.deb

    🔹 Only errors and warnings are displayed, removing other informational output, making the output cleaner.
